Reasoning: The paper describes a software package for solving eigenvalue problems using preconditioned iterative methods. This falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The package is designed to work with PETSc and hypre, which are commonly used for solving partial differential equations (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the scalability of the package on parallel systems, which is a topic of interest in high-performance computing (cs.MS). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of preconditioners, which are commonly used in scientific computing and computational engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper includes numerical experiments to demonstrate the performance of the package, which could be considered machine learning (cs.LG) in the sense that the authors are using empirical data to evaluate the effectiveness of their algorithm.
